<div id="review_3381956041" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3381956041" />
    <a title="Jonathan K" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/32433113-jonathan-k"><img alt="Jonathan K" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1404758116p2/32433113.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3381956041?book_show_action=true">Jul 12, 2020</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Jonathan K" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Jonathan K" href="/user/show/32433113-jonathan-k">Jonathan K</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Kindle Edition " href="/book/show/50412396-the-bone-collector">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3381956041" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer16628657608010314710"><strong>Creepy yet fascinating it takes forensic crime stories to a new level </strong><br/><br/>It&apos;s not often a character like Lincoln Rhyme is created. Paralyzed from the neck down, his encyclopedic brain coughs up remarkable forensic and historical elements associated with the crime. Battling with his inner demon, he&apos;s focused on ending his life until the bone collector surfaces in the form of a cab driver. A tour de force, the story engages at many levels and like all well crafted mysteries explodes with momentum tow</span>
  <span id="freeText16628657608010314710" style="display:none"><strong>Creepy yet fascinating it takes forensic crime stories to a new level </strong><br /><br />It's not often a character like Lincoln Rhyme is created. Paralyzed from the neck down, his encyclopedic brain coughs up remarkable forensic and historical elements associated with the crime. Battling with his inner demon, he's focused on ending his life until the bone collector surfaces in the form of a cab driver. A tour de force, the story engages at many levels and like all well crafted mysteries explodes with momentum towards the end. Having seen the Denzel Washington film, the book adds more depth, details, victims, characters and forensic crime solving details making it a more evocative experience. As it turns out, the screenplay flip flops the ethnicity of both Lincoln Rhyme and his caretaker and like many films, leaves out important plot elements. Regardless, Jeffrey Deaver is a master crime novelist and worth reading.</span>
  <a data-text-id="16628657608010314710" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


